<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
  <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8 text-center">Car Advertisements Web</h1>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Help & Documentation</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">Getting Started</h3>

  <div class="space-y-6">
    <div>
      <h4 class="font-semibold text-lg">1. Browse Cars</h4>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mt-1">
        Navigate to the Cars page to view all available car advertisements.
        You can sort by price, year, or mileage, and use pagination to browse through listings.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h4 class="font-semibold text-lg">2. Search for Specific Cars</h4>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mt-1">
        Use the Search page to filter cars by make, model, year range, and price range.
        This allows you to quickly find cars that match your criteria.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h4 class="font-semibold text-lg">3. Create an Account</h4>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mt-1">
        Sign up for an account to save your searches and access them later.
        This is useful if you're actively looking for a car and want to track specific criteria.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h3>

  <div class="space-y-6">
    <div>
      <h4 class="font-semibold text-lg">How do I save a search?</h4>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mt-1">
        You must be logged in to save searches. After performing a search,
        click the <span class="font-medium">"Save Search"</span> button to store your search criteria.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h4 class="font-semibold text-lg">How do I sort the car listings?</h4>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mt-1">
        On the Cars page, use the dropdown menu to select a sorting option.
        You can sort by price (low to high or high to low), year, or mileage.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h4 class="font-semibold text-lg">How many results are shown per page?</h4>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mt-1">
        By default, <span class="font-medium">10 results</span> are shown per page.
        Use the pagination controls at the bottom of the page to navigate through additional results.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h4 class="font-semibold text-lg">Is this a real car marketplace?</h4>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mt-1">
        This is only a learning project demonstrating Rails and Tailwind CSS integration.
        All data is for demonstration purposes.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="bg-gray-100 p-5 rounded mt-10 border border-gray-200">
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Need More Help?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">
      This is a demo application for learning purposes. For questions about implementation,
      refer to the Rails documentation or the project README.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="mt-10 text-center">
    <%= link_to "Back to home page", root_path,
        class: "inline-block bg-purple-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg shadow hover:bg-purple-700 transition duration-200" %>
  </div>
</div>
